commText: Saha and Shubman Gill are at the crease. Saha is on strike. Bhuvneshwar will open the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Saha, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, dabbed with an open face to the left of backward point - the fielder dives and gets a hand onto it, but he can't prevent the single

Bhuvneshwar to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, nicely played, fraction fuller and wider of off - Gill stabs with an open face and it needed a sliding effort from Shahbaz in front of the ropes to prevent the boundary
Bhuvneshwar to Shubman Gill, no run, on a good length and just outside off - Gill leans across and steers it straight to the fielder at backward point
Bhuvneshwar to Shubman Gill, no run, tad fuller and wider of off, Gill leans into the drive and finds mid-off
Bhuvneshwar to Shubman Gill, FOUR, cracking shot, width on offer from Bhuvneshwar - Gill leans across, head on top of the ball and then crunches the drive square past cover, no need to run for those
Bhuvneshwar to Shubman Gill, no run, on a good length and angling into the right-hander, Gill stumbled across on the flick, closed the bat-face and gets a soft edge back at the bowler
Spin and it's Shahbaz Ahmed
Shahbaz Ahmed, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Shahbaz Ahmed to Saha, 1 run, tossed up on the leg-stump line, flicked past mid-wicket for a single
Shahbaz Ahmed to Shubman Gill, 1 run, flatter and just outside off, pushed down to long-off for a single

Shahbaz Ahmed to Saha, SIX, beautifully played, flighted delivery and drifting into the right-hander - Saha clears his left leg, plays with the angle and then whips it over mid-wicket, clears the ropes for a maximum

Shahbaz Ahmed to Saha, 1 run, uppish and safe, flighted delivery on middle - Saha backed away and was looking to go inside out over cover, came off the inner half and has enough to clear the leaping bowler
Shahbaz Ahmed to Shubman Gill, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, tucked in front of square on the on-side for a single
Shahbaz Ahmed to Saha, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, punched down to long-off for a single
Bhuvneshwar to Saha, 1 run, banged in short and at the stumps, pulled to the right of mid-wicket where Markram makes a diving half-stop, keeping them down to a single

Bhuvneshwar to Shubman Gill, no run, back of a length and just outside off - brings out a half-hearted pull from Shubman, looked like he checked his shot at the last moment and the ball drops short of Markram at mid-wicket
Bhuvneshwar to Shubman Gill, no run, on a good length and angling into the right-hander, Gill prods across and nudges it to the on-side
Bhuvneshwar to Shubman Gill, 1 run, tad fuller and just outside off, nudged into the gap behind square on the off-side for a single
Bhuvneshwar to Saha, FOUR, hammered, Saha runs down the pitch, takes the momentum into the drive and gets enough to clear mid-off, bounces away to the ropes
Bhuvneshwar to Saha, 1 run, Bhuvneshwar drags the length back on middle, pulled behind square on the on-side for a single
Just one over for Shahbaz, he's replaced by Unadkat
Jaydev Unadkat, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Unadkat to Saha, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, driven to long-off for a single
Unadkat to Shubman Gill, 1 run, the slower cutter from Unadkat, Gill drops it in front of cover for a single

Unadkat to Saha, 1 run, Unadkat spotted Saha coming down the pitch, dragged the length back and slipped in the slower ball, Saha was early into the pull and gets an inside edge onto the pad, the ball rolling to the off-side
Unadkat to Shubman Gill, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, pushed down to long-off for a single
Unadkat to Saha, SIX, a gift and Saha accepts it with glee, full-toss on the pads and it's whipped away over square leg, went sailing into the crowd
Unadkat switches to round the wicket
Unadkat to Saha, 1 run, fuller length delivery on off, pushed in front of mid-on for a quick single, 11 off the over
Change of ends for Shahbaz
Shahbaz Ahmed [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Shahbaz Ahmed to Saha, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Shahbaz Ahmed to Saha, out Caught by Cummins!! Catching practice at mid-on - On a length and angling into the right-hander, Saha was looking to carve it over the on-side, but he doesn't get a lot of power behind the shot, chips it in the air and Cummins completes the catch, running back at mid-on. Saha c Cummins b Shahbaz Ahmed 25(13) [4s-1 6s-2]
GT have activated their impact substitute - Sai Sudharsan replaces Mohit Sharma
Sai Sudharsan, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Shahbaz Ahmed to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, flatter and at the pads, whipped through mid-wicket for a single
Shahbaz Ahmed to Shubman Gill, no run, tossed up on middle and leg, pushed to mid-on
Shahbaz Ahmed to Shubman Gill, SIX, beautifully played, Gill skips down the pitch, makes room and then launches the drive over extra-cover, went sailing over the ropes
Shahbaz Ahmed to Shubman Gill, 1 run, Shahbaz drags the length back outside off, driven down to long-off for a single
Shahbaz Ahmed to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, tossed up on off, whipped through mid-wicket for a single

Over Summary (1-5 ov) * Gill gets into the groove with a cracking boundary * Saha smashes a maximum to find his feet as well * Saha continues to blossom by finding boundaries regularly * Change of ends works for Shahbaz as he cuts Saha’s cameo short * Gill lofts one over extra cover off Shahbaz’s bowling to keep things moving
Bhuvneshwar Kumar [2.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Sai Sudharsan, no run, short of a good length and on off, punched off the back-foot to mid-on
Bhuvneshwar to Sai Sudharsan, no run, on a length and just outside off, punched off the back-foot to cover
Bhuvneshwar to Sai Sudharsan, no run, short of a good length and just outside off, Sudharsan hacks without any timing and the ball rolls to mid-wicket

Bhuvneshwar to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, lovely, length ball on the pads, Sudharsan lets the ball come, brings his wrists into play and then plays an exquisite on-drive, beats mid-wicket to his left and races away
Bhuvneshwar to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, on a length and at the pads, clipped in front of square on the on-side - Abishek is put under pressure and he fumbles, allowing a second run
Bhuvneshwar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, short of a good length and at the pads, flicked in front of square on the on-side for a single
The physio is out to tend to Gill. He should be fine to resume. Impact Player vs Impact Player...
Washington Sundar, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Washington Sundar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 89.3kph, round the wicket, non-turner darted in on the stumps, punched to the right of long-off
Over the wicket to Shubman Gill
Washington Sundar to Shubman Gill, no run, 102.9kph, short of length, Gill punches to midwicket
Washington Sundar to Shubman Gill, 1 run, 94.8kph, Gill makes room and chops this non-turner towards cover
Washington Sundar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 101.4kph, width on offer, cut to sweeper cover

Washington Sundar to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, 103.6kph, fuller on leg, worked in front of square on the leg-side and Gill straightaway calls for two. Markram attacks the ball but fails to pick it up cleanly
Washington Sundar to Shubman Gill, 1 run, leg-lined, tucked through backward square leg
Spin from both ends now
Mayank Markande, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Markande to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, 84.2kph, fullish leggie just outside off, driven to the left of extra cover
Markande to Shubman Gill, 1 run, 90.6kph, in-drifter, knocked to long-on
Markande to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 94.8kph, leg-lined, nudged towards square leg
Markande to Shubman Gill, 1 run, 76.2kph, slower and slightly shorter, Gill turns it to midwicket
Markande to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 95.1kph, googly outside off, Sai Sudharsan reaches out to cut, miscues and backward point takes it on the bounce
Markande to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 83.1kph, shimmies down the pitch to drive and Markande stops it with a dive to his right in his followthrough
Washington Sundar to Shubman Gill, 1 run, 102.2kph, shortish ball, pulled to deep midwicket
Washington Sundar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 102.7kph, Sundar not looking to spin the ball, Sai Sudharsan stays in his crease and bunts it to long-on
Washington Sundar to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, 103.9kph, pulled to deep square leg for a couple more
Washington Sundar to Shubman Gill, FOUR, 104.2kph, Sundar bowls this too straight and Shubman Gill pounces. Uses the bowler's pace and angle to his advantage. Half-pulls it square of the man at 45
Washington Sundar to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, 103.8kph, turns this fuller ball in front of square on the leg-side and comes back for the second. Very good running
Washington Sundar to Shubman Gill, 1 run, 100.9kph, backs away and chops this straight ball to deep point

Timeout! Saha departed after a brisk start, Gill is looking in good touch and GT will be the happier side. Washington Sundar has been bowling darts so far and hasn't been threatening. Captain Cummins is yet to bowl. Can the visitors exert pressure?
Markande to Shubman Gill, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Markande to Shubman Gill, out Caught by Abdul Samad!! A wicket immediately after the timeout and it's the set batter! 84.6kph, tossed up, scrambled seam, full around leg and probably off the front of the hand. The GT captain shimmies down the track in an attempt to loft it over wide long-on. Gets too close to the pitch of the ball and gets it off the bottom part of the bat. Samad moves to his right from long-on to take a safe catch. Much-needed wicket for SRH! Shubman Gill c Abdul Samad b Markande 36(28) [4s-2 6s-1]
David Miller, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Markande to Miller, 1 run, knocks this fullish ball to long-on
Markande to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, swept to deep backward square leg
Markande to Miller, 1 run, 83.4kph, googly from a shortened length, slapped to sweeper cover off the back foot
Markande to Sai Sudharsan, no run, another one that goes away with the angle outside off, Sai Sudharsan tries to steer it towards third man and gets beaten on the outside edge
Markande to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 80.9kph, flighted outside off, Sai Sudharsan leans across to drive it to deep cover

Over Summary (6-10 ov) * Sudharsan finds the fence with a lovely on-drive * SRH’s Impact sub, Washington Sundar, begins with a tidy 6-run over * Markande backs up Sundar’s start with another miserly 5-run over * Sundar concedes 11 runs in his 2nd over * Markande changes the flow of the game by getting the well-set Gill * Only 33 runs are scored at the loss of a wicket in this phase of play
Here's the SRH captain from round the wicket
Pat Cummins, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Cummins to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 116.5kph, pace off and into the wicket, Sai Sudharsan has to wait before punching it wide of cover. Came slower than he expected
Cummins to Miller, 1 run, 138.9kph, rib-tickler, tucked to fine leg
Cummins to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 140.2kph, fuller than a length, Sai Sudharsan gets forward to play a wristy drive to long-on
Cummins to Miller, 1 run, 114.7kph, slower delivery, Miller waits and dabs it to third man
Cummins to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 113.5kph, pace off again, short of length around off, pulled to long-on
Cummins to Miller, no run, 138.6kph, pace on, in-slanter on middle and that's been turned to midwicket. Tidy opening over from Cummins
Jaydev Unadkat [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Unadkat to Sai Sudharsan, no run, fuller than a length, a shuffling Sai Sudharsan drives to mid-off
Unadkat to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 114.3kph, slower ball into the wicket, Sai Sudharsan pulls to deep midwicket
Unadkat to Miller, no run, 107.3kph, pace off again, the length is fuller, Miller stays leg-side and drills it straight to extra cover
Unadkat to Miller, 1 run, 110.1kph, length ball around off, probably the cutter, chopped towards point
Unadkat to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, 129.9kph, Sai Sudharsan breaks the shackles. Unadkat goes fuller and Sai Sudharsan drives aerially. Over the bowler and straight of mid-off

Unadkat to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 106.7kph, slower ball to end the over, Sai Sudharsan picks it and is still early to close his bat-face. The ball holds onto the pitch a bit and hits the splice of the bat before rolling towards point
Equation: 73 runs | 48 balls!
Cummins to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 120.7kph, pace off and shortish ball, Sai Sudharsan swivels and miscues the pull to square leg
Cummins to Miller, no run, off-cutter into the wicket, Miller is early to swing his bat and fails to make contact
Cummins to Miller, 1 run, 142.4kph, a backing away Miller hurriedly dabs this in-slanter to third man
Cummins to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 120.9kph, slower ball into the wicket, Sai Sudharsan swings to pull and gets an under-edge that goes to the keeper on the bounce
Cummins to Sai Sudharsan, wide, slow bumper, Sai Sudharsan lets it pass as it goes over his head
Third man comes inside the circle!
Cummins to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, 139.7kph, superb placement! Pace on,
Cummins to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 119.6kph, pace off and straighter line, nudged into the midwicket pocket for a single

Timeout! The phase between the two breaks - 4 overs | 24 runs | 1 wicket. This game is nicely poised. GT have eight wickets in hand and SRH will rely on varying the pace. Equation: 65 runs | 42 balls.
Washington Sundar [2.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Washington Sundar to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, 86.1kph, short of length, leg-lined and the batter pounces. Sai Sudharsan bends his back leg and pulls it thugh backward square leg
Washington Sundar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 89.9kph, fuller length and that's been square-driven for a single
Washington Sundar to Miller, 2 runs, 98.4kph, Miller moves leg-side to cut it to deep point. Miller calls for the second and makes his ground with a dive
Washington Sundar to Miller, 1 run, 90.4kph, shortened length, chopped wide of cover
Washington Sundar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 99.3kph, quick offie, nudged towards midwicket
Washington Sundar to Miller, 1 run, non-turner on a length wide of off, Miller backs away and cuts to sweeper cover. 10 runs off the over
Equation: 55 runs | 36 balls. With two left-handers in the crease, will Cummins turn to Markande? It's Bhuvi for now...
Bhuvneshwar Kumar [3.0-0-21-0] is back into the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Miller, 1 run, 127.1kph, short ball, Miller waits and slams the pull to deep midwicket
Bhuvneshwar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 127.5kph, slow and short, Sai Sudharsan arches back and elevates it over vacant first slip. A single to third man
Bhuvneshwar to Miller, 1 run, 127kph, short of a good length, Miller stays leg-side and knocks it in front of mid-off for a single. Miller limps to take the single!
Bhuvneshwar to Sai Sudharsan, wide, 128.5kph, too short outside off, a hopping Sai Sudharsan fails to make contact as he tries to upper-cut it towards third man
Bhuvneshwar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 127.8kph, back of a length, tucked to deep midwicket
Bhuvneshwar to Miller, no run, 121kph, slower delivery, Miller chops it to cover

Bhuvneshwar to Miller, 1 run, 127.1kph, slower ball wide of off from a short of length, Miller looks to cut and under-edges towards third man. Bhuvneshwar goes wicketless again but he's been economical today (0/27)

Over Summary (11-15 ov) * Cummins introduces himself in the 11th over & only concedes 5 runs * Sudharsan & Miller struggle for rhythm as the slower balls from the pacers grip * Sudharsan breaks the shackles with a boundary in the 12th over * Sudharsan keeps GT in the contest by scoring another boundary in the 13th over * Sundar concedes a boundary off his first ball in his second spell * Bhuvneshwar finishes his spell with a tight 6-run over * The game hangs in the balance with GT needing 49 off 30 balls
Equation: 49 runs | 30 balls. Cummins has summoned the wrist spinner. This could turn out to be a crucial over
Mayank Markande [2.0-0-9-1] is back into the attack
Markande to Miller, wide, 85.7kph, googly, too wide outside off and Miller shoulders arms

Markande to Miller, FOUR, 81.9kph, slow googly but the length is on the shorter side. Miller waits on the back foot and slams it over midwicket for a one-bounce four. Split the gap between long-on and deep midwicket
Markande to Miller, FOUR, 89.8kph, use of the feet! Miller shimmies down and carves this wide-ish ball over extra cover. One bounce and into the fence
Markande to Miller, wide, 87.4kph, second wide of the over as he bowls this wrong 'un outside the tramline outside off
Markande to Miller, 1 run, 87.7kph, Miller looks to punch through the covers and inside-edges to short fine leg
Markande to Sai Sudharsan, SIX, 87.6kph high and handsome! Waltzes down the pitch, gets close to the pitch of this fullish ball and bludgeons it over wide long-on
Markande to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, chopped through cover

Markande to Miller, SIX, big over! This was always going to be a gamble. A leggie against two left-handers and GT have punished him. Miller shimmies down, converts it into a half-volley and lofts it downtown. 24 runs off the over!
Equation: 25 runs | 24 balls!
Pat Cummins [2.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack
Cummins to Sai Sudharsan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Cummins to Sai Sudharsan, out Caught by Abhishek Sharma!! Gone! Is there still life left in this contest? 119.8kph, slower ball into the wicket, Sai Sudharsan spots it and goes after it with a pull shot. Connects well but hits it flat to deep midwicket. Abhishek holds onto the catch and the 64-run stand has been broken. Sai Sudharsan c Abhishek Sharma b Cummins 45(36) [4s-4 6s-1]
Vijay Shankar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Cummins to Shankar, no run, low full toss on off, Shankar drives it straight to cover
Cummins to Shankar, 1 run, banged in short, Shankar miscues the hook towards fine leg
Cummins to Miller, FOUR, 116.8kph, Miller probably expected this slower ball. Waits, swivels and pulls this shortish ball through backward square leg
Cummins to Miller, no run, Cummins goes fuller and wider, Miller leans and drives straight to extra cover

Cummins to Miller, FOUR, 116.1kph, slow, short and outside off, Miller stands tall to slap it to the right of extra cover. That should have been stopped but the fielder lets the ball burst through his fingers and the ball speeds away to the fence
Equation: 16 runs | 18 balls
Jaydev Unadkat [2.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack

Unadkat to Shankar, FOUR, 111.2kph, round the wicket, slower ball bumper, Shankar is way too early into his pull and gets a top-edge that ballons up over the keeper. Klaasen gives a chase and tries his best by sliding but to no avail
Unadkat to Shankar, FOUR, top shot! 105.7kph, pace off again, Shankar makes room and punches it up and over wide mid-off. Back-to-back boundaries!
Unadkat to Shankar, no run, 128.9kph, fuller length ball and that's been push-driven to extra cover

Unadkat to Shankar, no run, 109.3kph, slower ball into the wicket, Shankar is early into his pull. The ball goes towards short third man off his helmet and Miller doesn't want to take the single! He was seen limping as well, that could be the reason
Unadkat to Shankar, no run, 124kph, full delivery, Shankar clips it to midwicket and once again single not taken
Unadkat to Shankar, 1 run, 106kph, pace off and full in length, driven down to long-off and now they take the single
Equation: 7 runs | 12 balls.
Cummins to Shankar, 1 run, 145.6kph, pacy bumper, hurriedly pulled to deep square leg
Cummins to Miller, 1 run, 119kph, pulled to deep square leg
Cummins to Shankar, 1 run, pacy yorker, squeezed to long-on
Cummins to Miller, no run, 146.1kph, another one in the blockhole, Miller can only jam it back at the bowler
Change of ball. Don't think Cummins is too happy with the replacement ball
Cummins to Miller, 1 run, slow, short and wide of off, Miller waits to chop it to deep point

Cummins to Shankar, 2 runs, 143.6kph, skiddy short ball, swivel-pulled to deep backward square leg and even a hobbling Miller decides to come back for the second. The throw comes to the wrong (keeper's) end
Just one run needed off the final over.
Unadkat to Miller, SIX, Miller finishes in style! 106.3kph, slow, full and in the slot outside off, Miller gets under it and lofts it handsomely over long-off. Gujarat Titans win by 7 wickets!

18:54 Local Time, 13:24 GMT, 18:54 IST: Clinical from Gujarat. Their bowlers set it up with an impressive performance in the afternoon as they restricted a dangerous SRH batting line-up to 162 on a slightly two-paced surface. Mohit Sharma was the pick of the bowlers as he picked a three-fer and the Afghan spin twins - Noor and Rashid - bowled well in the middle overs. In reply, Saha got his team off to a brisk start before perishing to Shahbaz in the powerplay. Shubman Gill got a start and looked in good touch but he holed out immediately after the strategic timeout. SRH exerted some pressure on the hosts with a couple of tight overs. However, Sai Sudharsan and Miller never panicked. Washington Sundar, the Impact Player, wasn't effective and the two left-handers went after Markande in the 16th overs which went for 24 runs (Wd 4 4 Wd 1 6 1 6). That turned out to be the decisive over. Cummins managed to nip out Sai and somehow dragged the match to the final over but Miller, despite hobbling, showed his prowess to take his team home.

Pat Cummins | SRH captain: Good game of cricket, was tight in the end, probably we needed 10-15 more runs. I think they bowled well, just losing a couple of wickets, didn’t have that one person who kicked on to get a fifty, that happens. Today it was, we thought the wicket was going to get a bit slow, the off-cutters did grip, we had 8 bowling options in our side. I thought the wicket played the same in both innings. It’s T20 cricket isn’t it? Had a fantastic couple of games with the bat, today we didn’t quite click.

Sai Sudharsan: I'm happy that my contribution helped the team win, so definitely happy. It was a difficult wicket to play the fast bowlers, bowling into the pitch was hard to score off, so we decided to target that one over of spin. Great contributions from Mohit bhai and Rashid bhai, picked crucial wickets and restricted the target by around 10-15 runs. Playing in front of the home crowd is a plus point for us. Everyone wants to get more runs, I just want to contribute my best, milestones will happen by itself.

Gujarat Titans in run-chases in the IPL Matches: 20 Won: 15 Lost: 5 W/L ratio: 3 Their win-loss ratio while chasing is the joint highest for any team in the IPL, alongside Gujarat Lions, who won 12 and lost four batting second across the 2016 and 2017 editions.

David Miller in successful run-chases in the IPL Inns: 31 Runs: 1020 Avg: 113.33 SR: 149.12 50/100: 6/1 HS: 101* Of the 379 players who have batted at least once in a successful IPL run-chase, Miller’s average of 113.33 is the highest.
Stats round-up by Roshan Gede

Shubman Gill | GT captain: To be able to win two matches at home, great. Our next match is also here and then we've got a couple of matches on the road. Hopefully by the time we come back, we will have good momentum into this tournament. The way our bowlers bowled in the middle overs, especially Noor ... obviously Rashid bhai is a world-class bowler and he's always coming in and giving his best, but the way Darshan came in and bowled those two crucial overs at the death was very important for us. (On Mohit) He's such an experienced player, especially on wickets like these. He comes in day in day out, he practises his skills and he's so skilled. It's not easy in this heat to bowl four overs back-to-back, sometimes three overs back-to-back. But he comes in, bowls those yorkers, slower ones and mixes it so well. The credit has to go to him for practising those skills and to be able to have the confidence to execute them in the match. In this heat, wherever we play in the day match, it's easier to score with the new ball. Once the ball gets old and the wickets gets slow, it's difficult to hit those sixes, especially on the longer side and that was our plan - to be able to let them hit the slower ones on the longer side. (On his dismissal) The ball was there to be hit, I was just backing my shot, but the ball hit the bottom and it didn't bounce as much as I expected it to be but that's fine. In T20, you have to always keep your options open and if the ball is there, you have to go for it. Once we saw how our spinners were bowling, we thought 160-170 would be a good score. Credit to the bowlers how they came in and restricted them to that total. Everybody knows their roles in terms of batting or bowling, Sai has been playing well, Wriddhi bhai has been doing what Wriddhi bhai does and it was important for us to be able to get Miller back in form. Just cramps (on Miller's status).

Mohit Sharma | Player of the Match: Thank you sir for reminding me that I’m getting older day by day (chuckles). Practice is normal but the important thing is how to use the variation according to the game situation. Bowlers do have variations but it matters when and how to use it. It’s important when you have two balls in mind, the batters are also ready, they are ready for the slower bouncer but they are not ready for the slower short ball wide of the wicket so I mix and match. Dew is uncontrollable and we practice bowling with a wet ball. When it’s going good, I enjoy. When the match gets over, I like to reflect where I did well and where I didn’t. Rashid and Noor bowled well, we went for a few runs in the back end but we came back well in the final few overs.
